******************************************************************************************************
******************************************************************************************************
Thanks for using the modified Goldstein filter!
We apply the frequency spectrum coefficient variation into the determination of filtering parameter α.
The modified filter performs better in the reduction of phase unwrapping residues and phase noise.

******************************************************************************************************
Here are the instructions for the interpretation and operation of the package.

******************************************************************************************************
The program is written in Matlab.

1. "main.m" : the main function of the program running.

2. "fringe_estimate_coarse" & "fringe_reconstruction_corase" : used for fringe reconstruction and removal.

3. "cv_goldstein_sim" : used for interferogram filtering.

4. "cv_calculation" :used for the calculation of CV in one unit patch.

5. "cv_main" : used for the calculation of CV in the whole interferogram.

6. "cv_alpha_fit" : used for curve fitting between CV and α.

7. "index_model" : used for evaluating the fitered interferogram.

8. "wrap" : wrap interferometric phase for function 7.

functions 4~6 are all applied in function 3.


******************************************************************************************************
To test the modified filter, you just need to run the "main" file.

******************************************************************************************************
Test data is stored under the same path as the "main" file, named "sim_phase_with_noise_two_look.dat";

and the output files are stored in the folder "Results" in .tiff.

******************************************************************************************************
******************************************************************************************************
